Package: squr
Title: Structured Query Utility for R
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: c(
  person("Elias", "Joran", email = "joran.elias@gmail.com", role = c("aut","cre")),
  person("Stefan Milton", "Bache", email = "stefan@stefanbache.dk", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: squr (pronounce 'skewer' /'skju:əɹ/)
  is a small utility that provides a set of tools
  for managing structured query language (SQL) files in R projects.
  It promotes the separation of logic and query scripts and eases the process
  of reading, parameterizing, and composing SQL queries.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.0)
Imports:
    magrittr, 
    DBI,
    purrr,
    stringr
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests:
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
